SS109 is "armor piercing", in other words, light armor (helmets, body armor, etc.). However, it is not "cop killer" ammo like some say. It is probably the best all around ammo. title: For Sale:  Colt -- Model 1862 Police 36 Cal 1st Yr Production
postcontent: This is one of those hard to find first year production Colt Model 1862 Police Revolvers that is better than fine but not quite excellent according to NRA definition. According to Flayderman’s, the Model 1862 is considered by many collectors as the ultimate in streamlined design by Colt’s factory during the percussion period. The 4 digit serial number of this gun indicates that it was manufactured in 1861. 36 Cal.5 shot. This one has a 4 ½” round barrel with the COL. SAML COLT NEW YORK USA AMERICA barrel address. COLTS/PATENT is stamped on the left side of the frame and PAT SEPT 10TH 1850 is stamped within one of the cylinder flutes. Serial number matches the cylinder, frame, trigger guard, arbor, back strap and wedge. Nipples are in good condition. There is evidence of 4 remaining safety pins. The gun retains a great deal of color. The trigger and wedge has a high percentage of blue while the bottom four screws and loading lever screws retain their fire blue finish. The frame has a high percentage of case coloring remaining. The back strap has a generous amount of tarnished silver at the butt and frame. The cylinder is plum brown with bluing in the cylinder stops. The barrel has about 50% of its blue. The bore has fine lands and grooves and is still shiny. The one piece varnished walnut grips are in excellent condition and retain at least 95% of the original varnish

title: For Sale:  Kel-Tec P3AT  .380 ACP Pistol
postcontent:
This Kel-Tec P3AT is a semi-automatic, locked breech pistol, chambered for the .380 Auto cartridge.  The firing mechanism is double action only. The magazine has a 6 round capacity.   It has been carried a lot, but fired very little, just enough to break it in and make it very reliable.  It's in excellent condition.

The KEL-TEC P3AT is the lightest .380 Auto pistol ever made.   It's mainly intended for plainclothes police officers as a secondary weapon, or for concealed carry by licensed citizens. The small grip size and light trigger pull make the P3AT ideal for female shooters.

The P3AT has five main component groups: barrel, slide, firing mechanism, grip, and magazine. The barrel is made of SAE 4140 ordnance steel.  The slide is also 4140 steel, and contains the firing pin and the extractor.  The rectangular frame is machined from solid 7075-T6 aluminum and houses the firing mechanism. The trigger connects via a transfer bar to the hammer.  After firing, the hammer block holds the hammer away from the firing pin, providing a mechanical safety. 

This little pistol is priced for immediate sale, cash only please.  Contact me to arrange a meeting place and time for your inspection.
